12- to 14-lb turkey (preferably kosher), any feathers and quills removed with tweezers or needlenose pliers, and neck and giblets (excluding liver) reserved	1		
all-purpose flour	1/3	cup	
chinese five-spice powder	2	teaspoons	
salt	1 1/2	teaspoons	
whole black peppercorns	2	tablespoons	
unsalted butter	1/2	stick	
dry red wine	1/2	cup	
turkey giblet stock	3 1/2	cups	
spinach, bacon, and cashew stuffing (see stuffed onions )	7	cups	
instant-read thermometer	1		
kitchen string			
pan juices from roast turkey			
small metal skewers or wooden toothpicks	2		
plum jam (preferably damson plum) or red currant jelly	3/4	cup	
